<br>
It gives me great pleasure to announce that Faerie Fire will be hosting a Grand Language Faire on Saturday, July the 12th, at 9pm CET (7pm GMT, 3pm EST, 12 noon PST). All those interested in participating are asked to please meet at the appointed time at the great statue, just inside the city of Sanctus Seru. For any who do not know the way, or who feel they will need assistance getting there, please feel free to leave word here, or to speak to me in the lands of Norrath! <br>
<br>
To accomodate the sensibilities of many of those in attendance, individuals of the darker races will be asked kindly not to attend. <br>
<br>
For the enjoyment of those in attendance, Sanctus Seru boasts many lovely pools and gardens, as well as some ~very~ large and well-stocked taverns! As drinking and language-learning do seem to occassionally lead to violence, Sanctus Seru also has one of the ~loveliest~ arenas in the known world! <br>
<br>
I hope to see you there with your Savant's Caps on! <br>
<br>
<br>
Ylandra Vaeratha, <br>
